In my project I've ended with function similar to (simpler, as I'm supporting Py3k only):

    def escape_filter_chars(text, encoding=None, escape=u'\\*()\0'):
        """ Escape chars mentioned in RFC4515. """
        if encoding is None:
            encoding = get_config_parameter('DEFAULT_ENCODING')
        text = to_unicode(text, encoding)
        for char in escape:
            text = text.replace(char, escape_bytes(to_raw(char)))
        return text

As for me it's useful to sometimes pass untouched `*` coming from user forms. Of course feel free to include this version (or any variation of it) in `utils.conv` (same applies to `is_filter_safe(text)`).

