Hi @dmarra!

You can use the [`output_formatContent` callback](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-output.html#output_formatcontent) to determine what is sent to the output widget... in this case you can send the content when it's processing the header and the parsed data otherwise ([demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/yL1qon7e/35/)):

```js
$(function() {

  var $table = $('table');

  $('.download').click(function() {
    $table.trigger('outputTable');
  });

  $table.tablesorter({
    theme: 'blue',
    widgets: ['zebra', 'output'],
    widgetOptions: {
      output_formatContent: function(c, wo, data) {
      	return data.isHeader ? data.content : data.parsed;
      }
    }
  });
});
```

